<TITLE> Academy rule Tasmania on Day 2 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 3 (bdnews24.com) The Bangladesh Academy team were in the driving seat against Tasmania taking an overall 295-run lead in the Crocodile Cup three-dayer at the University ground in Darwin, Monday. The academy side were 139 for six in the second innings at the close of the second day with Nayeem Islam and Sahagir Hossain Pavel batting with 29 and 34. Openers Imrul Kayes (5) and Mehrab Hossain (8) returned to the dressing room poorly, but Nasiruddin Faruque (27) and Rokibul Hasan (31) repaired the initial damage to take the side to 77 before being separated. After the departure of Faruque, Bangladesh saw a horrible collapse losing three quick wickets to stand at 77 for six while Nayeem and Sahagir steered the boat to rescue their side with remaining unbeaten at the end of Day 2. Chasing Academy's first innings total of 308 for seven declared, Tasmania, having resumed the day on five for no loss, ended up their first innings at 152 all out. Pacer Dollar Mahmud spearheaded the attack with three for 21 while his fellow pacers Nazmul Hossain and Mahbub Alam Robin took two wickets each for 21 and 38. Left-arm spinner Enamul Haq Jr also chipped in with two wickets for 25. 
